SIMPLE: fantasy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fantasy
<hw>Fan"ta*sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Fantasies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[See
<er>Fancy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fancy; imagination; especially,
a whimsical or fanciful conception; a vagary of the imagination; whim;
caprice; humor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Is not this something more than <qex>fantasy</qex> ?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A thousand <qex>fantasies</qex>⟦br⟧
Begin to throng into my memory.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fantastic designs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Embroidered with <qex>fantasies</qex> and flourishes of gold
thread.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fantasy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fantasy
<hw>Fan"ta*sy</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To have a fancy for; to be
pleased with; to like; to fancy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cavendish.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which he doth most <qex>fantasy</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Robynson
(More's Utopia).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fantique</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Fantigue</ent>⟦br⟧
